				<li>Opportunistic Encryption</li>
				<li>Any Page Rules redirecting traffic to HTTPS</li>
			</ul>
			<p>Similarly, any HTTP redirect to HTTPS at the origin while the Cloudflare proxy is enabled will result in users being unable to visit your site without a valid certificate at Cloudflare’s edge. </p>
			<p>If you do not have a valid custom or dedicated certificate at Cloudflare’s edge and are unsure if any of the above Cloudflare settings are enabled or if any HTTP redirects exist at your origin, we advise leaving Universal SSL enabled for your domain. For more help, please check our <a target="blank" href="https://support.cloudflare.com/hc/en-us/categories/200276247" >knowledge base</a>.</p>
